        introductions from ballast.</discussion>
  <discussion>The closely related Mexican and Central American Cyperus regiomontanus Britton has
        been collected once as an adventive or waif in southern California. It is distinguished from
        C. aggregatus by its silvery green, subulate-lanceolate spikelets and achenes that are only
        0.4–0.6 mm wide.</discussion>
